&quot;NODWICK&quot; Web Comic

&quot;Nodwick&quot; (nodwick.com) by Aaron Williams is a humorous comic based around the conventions of fantasy role-playing games, in particular &quot;Dungeons &amp; Dragons.&quot;  The titular character, Nodwick, is a henchman in the employ of a typical D&amp;D-style adventuring party consisting of Yeagar, a buff but moronic fighter, Artax, a semicompetent wizard, and Piffany, an unfailingly honest and hopelessly naive cleric of good.  The strip debuted in &quot;Dragon&quot; magazine in 1998, and ran fairly regularly until the magazine ceased publication in 2007.  &quot;Nodwick&quot; also appeared as a bimonthly comic book from 2000 until 2006.  The content of the comic books was reprinted online starting in 2008.  A &quot;reinvented&quot; version of Nodwick and his adventuring group also appeared in comics based on the &quot;City of Heroes&quot; MMORPG as the superhero team &quot;Q-4orce.&quot;

This torrent collects all 36 issues of the &quot;Nodwick&quot; comic book, though it should be noted that those issues are recreated from the images posted online, and are NOT actually scans of the books.  As well, as much of the &quot;Dragon&quot; magazine and online-only content is included as is still available (as of early 2015) in the online archive
